## üîë Connect Your Studio to the World

### API Configuration

Your studio needs these API keys to automate your media operations:

```bash
# Copy the template and add your keys
cp .env.example .env
```

**Required for Full Automation:**
- **TWITTER_API_KEY** - Monitor mentions, schedule posts, track engagement
- **OPENAI_API_KEY** - Power AI content creation and strategy
- **OPENROUTER_API_KEY** - Access multiple AI models for different tasks
- **FIRECRAWL_API_KEY** - Research competitor content and industry trends
- **DATABASE_URL** - Store your content, analytics, and audience data
- **GOOGLE_API_KEY** - Integrate with Google Sheets, Analytics, Drive

### Getting Your API Keys

#### Twitter API .io (Easiest Setup)
1. Go to [TwitterAPI.io](https://twitterapi.io/?ref=alexgirardet)
2. Sign up and get instant API access
3. Copy your API key - no OAuth complexity!

#### OpenAI API  
1. Visit [platform.openai.com](https://platform.openai.com)
2. Add billing info and create an API key
3. Start with $10 credit to test your workflows

#### OpenRouter API
1. Go to [openrouter.ai](https://openrouter.ai) 
2. Add credits and generate your API key
3. Access multiple AI models through one interface

#### Firecrawl API
1. Visit [firecrawl.dev](https://firecrawl.dev)
2. Create account and get your API key  
3. Perfect for automated research and monitoring

#### Database Setup
```bash
# For local development
DATABASE_URL=sqlite://./data.db

# For production (Supabase, Neon, etc.)
DATABASE_URL=postgresql://user:pass@host:port/dbname
```

